comments.body:
@rhatdan -- Could you clarify your intent here? 

I think we can both agree that the documentation in its current form is wrong, in the sense that it documents the existence of a `newer` pull policy that is invalid and not supported in `buildah`. I agree with your preference; it would be nice if podman and buildah both used the same set of pull policies, but that has not been true up to now.

Surely it is better to have documentation that is accurate to the current and actual state of the world rather than aspirational but wrong?
